definitions.definition: A boy who serves as a page .
A young male attendant at a wedding , generally between five and ten years of age .
A shoulder-length hairstyle with the ends of the hair curled under.

main_definition: ( now frequently historical ) A boy who serves as a page . [from 19th c.]
secondary_definitions: A young male attendant at a wedding , generally between five and ten years of age . [from 20th c.]
